content.message: [{'role': 'user', 'content': "Help me sort a list of items  myItemList alphabetically and ascendingly, but place items with a status of 'urgent' at the top, assuming the list is an array of objects with 'name' and 'status' properties?"}]

tools.name: prioritizeAndSort
tools.description: Display name: prioritize and sort items. Callable name: prioritizeAndSort. This function sorts an array of objects based on their 'name' property, while prioritizing items based on a specified status. Note that the provided function is in JavaScript syntax.

items.description: The array of objects to be sorted. This is JavaScript array type parameter in string representation. The list elements are of type String; they are not in string representation.

priorityStatus.description: The status value that should be given priority in the sorting. This is JavaScript String type parameter in string representation.

ascending.description: A flag indicating whether the sorting should be in ascending (true) or descending (false) order, excluding priority items. This is JavaScript Boolean type parameter in string representation.
